  "prompt": "What are some of the most common examples of an imperative sentence?",
  "response": "Imperative sentences give commands, instructions, or requests. Here are some common examples:\n\n1. **Close the door.**\n2. **Please pass the salt.**\n3. **Take a seat.**\n4. **Turn off the lights.**\n5. **Stop talking.**\n6. **Wash your hands.**\n7. **Read the instructions carefully.**\n8. **Listen to the teacher.**\n9. **Don't forget your keys.**\n10. **Help me with this task.**\n\nThese sentences typically begin with a verb and may include a subject (usually \"you,\" which is implied).",
